{"description":"\nDisplays short, contextual information about an item. Change the border\nand text color via the `color` prop. Use the `margin` prop to add space around\nthe component. Use the `renderIcon` prop to add an icon to the left of the text. Additionally,\nyou can use the `statusLabel` prop to add a label to the left of the main text.\n\n```js\n---\ntype: example\n---\n<div>\n  <div>\n    <Pill\n      margin=\"x-small\"\n    >\n      Excused\n    </Pill>\n    <Pill\n      statusLabel=\"Status\"\n      color=\"info\"\n      margin=\"x-small\"\n    >\n      Draft\n    </Pill>\n    <Pill\n      statusLabel=\"Status\"\n      renderIcon={<IconCheckLine />}\n      color=\"success\"\n      margin=\"x-small\"\n    >\n      Checked In\n    </Pill>\n    <Pill\n      renderIcon={<IconEndLine />}\n      color=\"danger\"\n      margin=\"x-small\"\n    >\n      Missing\n    </Pill>\n    <Pill\n      renderIcon={<IconClockLine />}\n      color=\"warning\"\n      margin=\"x-small\"\n    >\n      Late\n    </Pill>\n    <Pill\n      renderIcon={<IconMessageLine />}\n      color=\"alert\"\n      margin=\"x-small\"\n    >\n      Notification\n    </Pill>\n  </div>\n  <div>\n    <Pill_11_5\n      margin=\"x-small\"\n    >\n      Excused\n    </Pill_11_5>\n    <Pill_11_5\n      statusLabel=\"Status\"\n      color=\"info\"\n      margin=\"x-small\"\n    >\n      Draft\n    </Pill_11_5>\n    <Pill_11_5\n      statusLabel=\"Status\"\n      renderIcon={<IconCheckLine />}\n      color=\"success\"\n      margin=\"x-small\"\n    >\n      Checked In\n    </Pill_11_5>\n    <Pill_11_5\n      renderIcon={<IconEndLine />}\n      color=\"danger\"\n      margin=\"x-small\"\n    >\n      Missing\n    </Pill_11_5>\n    <Pill_11_5\n      renderIcon={<IconClockLine />}\n      color=\"warning\"\n      margin=\"x-small\"\n    >\n      Late\n    </Pill_11_5>\n    <Pill_11_5\n      renderIcon={<IconMessageLine />}\n      color=\"alert\"\n      margin=\"x-small\"\n    >\n      Notification\n    </Pill_11_5>\n  </div>\n</div>\n```\n\nThe component has a `max-width`, set by its theme. Any overflowing text will be handled via ellipses.\n\n> **DEPRECATED** Please do not make Pills that have overflowing text, it's an a11y anti-pattern. The issue is if text overflows it cannot be read by keyboard-only users. We could make the Pill focusable, but that would be an anti-pattern too because only elements that are interactive should be focusable (and just displaying a tooltip is not a real interaction)\n\n```js\n---\ntype: example\n---\n<Pill>\n  Supercalifragilisticexpialidocious bear\n</Pill>\n```\n\n### Guidelines\n\n```js\n---\ntype: embed\n---\n<Guidelines>\n  <Figure recommendation=\"no\" title=\"Don't\">\n    <Figure.Item>Use more than 2 words for the main text</Figure.Item>\n    <Figure.Item>Use more than 2 words for the statusLabel</Figure.Item>\n    <Figure.Item>Use for dismissible items (use a <Link href=\"/#Tag\">Tag</Link> instead)</Figure.Item>\n    <Figure.Item>Use for counts (use a <Link href=\"/#Badge\">Badge</Link> instead)</Figure.Item>\n    <Figure.Item>Put actions next to the text</Figure.Item>\n  </Figure>\n</Guidelines>\n```\n","displayName":"Pill","methods":[{"name":"setTruncation","docblock":null,"modifiers":[],"params":[],"returns":null},{"name":"handleRef","docblock":null,"modifiers":[],"params":[{"name":"el","optional":false,"type":{"name":"union","raw":"Element | null","elements":[{"name":"Element"},{"name":"null"}]}}],"returns":null},{"name":"renderPill","docblock":null,"modifiers":[],"params":[{"name":"focused","optional":true,"type":{"name":"TooltipRenderChildrenArgs['focused']","raw":"TooltipRenderChildrenArgs['focused']"}},{"name":"getTriggerProps","optional":true,"type":{"name":"TooltipRenderChildrenArgs['getTriggerProps']","raw":"TooltipRenderChildrenArgs['getTriggerProps']"}}],"returns":null}],"props":{"as":{"required":false,"tsType":{"name":"AsElementType"},"description":""},"color":{"required":false,"tsType":{"name":"union","raw":"'primary' | 'success' | 'danger' | 'info' | 'warning' | 'alert'","elements":[{"name":"literal","value":"'primary'"},{"name":"literal","value":"'success'"},{"name":"literal","value":"'danger'"},{"name":"literal","value":"'info'"},{"name":"literal","value":"'warning'"},{"name":"literal","value":"'alert'"}]},"description":"","defaultValue":{"value":"'primary'","computed":false}},"elementRef":{"required":false,"tsType":{"name":"signature","type":"function","raw":"(element: Element | null) => void","signature":{"arguments":[{"type":{"name":"union","raw":"Element | null","elements":[{"name":"Element"},{"name":"null"}]},"name":"element"}],"return":{"name":"void"}}},"description":"Provides a reference to the underlying HTML element"},"margin":{"required":false,"tsType":{"name":"Spacing"},"description":"Valid values are `0`, `none`, `auto`, `xxx-small`, `xx-small`, `x-small`,\n`small`, `medium`, `large`, `x-large`, `xx-large`. Apply these values via\nfamiliar CSS-like shorthand. For example: `margin=\"small auto large\"`."},"children":{"required":true,"tsType":{"name":"ReactReactNode","raw":"React.ReactNode"},"description":""},"statusLabel":{"required":false,"tsType":{"name":"string"},"description":"Adds a status label to the left of the main text."},"renderIcon":{"required":false,"tsType":{"name":"ReactReactNode","raw":"React.ReactNode"},"description":"An icon displayed to the left of the text."}},"category":"components","relativePath":"packages/ui-pill/src/Pill/index.tsx","extension":".tsx","srcPath":"packages/ui-pill/src/Pill/index.tsx","srcUrl":"https://github.com/instructure/instructure-ui/tree/master/packages/ui-pill/src/Pill/index.tsx","packageName":"@instructure/ui-pill","requirePath":"@instructure/ui-pill/lib/Pill/index","requireStr":"require('/home/runner/work/instructure-ui/instructure-ui/packages/ui-pill/src/Pill/index.tsx').default","esPath":"@instructure/ui-pill/es/Pill/index","themePath":"packages/ui-pill/src/Pill/styles.ts","themeUrl":"https://github.com/instru